description_jci_Inter:
The Junior Chamber International was founded in 1915 under the name of the Association of Young Men for Civic Progress by Henry Giessenbier. It became Junior Chamber International on December 11, 1944, when representatives from eight nations gathered to create an organization that would address global issues.

Junior Chamber International (JCI) is a global federation of 200,000 young professionals and entrepreneurs, aged 18 to 40, spread across nearly 5,000 communities in over 100 countries worldwide.JCI's mission is to provide young people with the necessary development opportunities to empower them to create "positive change" and aims to be the leading global network of active young citizens. This is something that JCI members have not failed to do. Around the world, they are active, dynamic, influential, and generally hold important positions in their respective societies.

description_jci_Tunisia: The Junior Chamber Economic of Tunisia (JCET) was founded in 1961. Thanks to its active participation in economic and social fields, it was classified among the organizations of national interest by decree No. 83/115 dated February 12, 1983. The Junior Chamber Economic of Tunisia encompasses a National Business Network called "Tunisian Business Network", which brings together businesspeople among the 5,000 members of the organization. This network strengthens business relations among its members, develops their leadership qualities, supports internal information and communication, and enhances contact with JCE Tunisia partners. The main focus of the network for the next five years will primarily revolve around the Maghreb Market "realities and perspectives". The 60 years of JCET's existence have been marked by exemplary support from its first partner and sponsor UTICA, allowing it to be the organization of leaders with an entrepreneurial spirit and economic development.
description_jci_HammamSousse: Founded on August 30, 1983, and officially adopted on April 8, 1984, during the 1st quarterly meeting in Sfax. From the appointment of the founding president of OLM Hammam Sousse, Mr. Mohamed DJEGHAM, the Junior Chamber International of Hammam Sousse has continuously served the local, national, and international community based on the six points of the creed and the four opportunities of the Junior Chamber (Individual, Community, Internationalism, Business).
